{"author":{"id":"6da5b2dec6684e0fa0fdf37f95430cd11b5c1f44f89e673d57db05c9808aaf42"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1516889013,"nonce":"FHfkRrbEk4vltBZ7uGesxzudBXw=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUyOTE1ODAzMzU=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/1688","origin":"github"},"title":"Mothur screen.seqs with a contigs report","message":"Hello everyone,\n\nOne of my colleague that uses Mothur for her analysis recently show me that there are two issues with the current Screen.seqs wrapper when you execute it with an input contigs report file (generated by Make.contigs).\n\nThe first one is that the option displayed in the help of the contigsreport parameter (Ie. minoverlap, ostart, oend and mismatches) can't be set with the current Screen.seqs wrapper.\n\nThe second one is that, in these conditions, Mothur generates a modified contigsreport (as displayed in its log) that is not recovered by the wrapper.\n\nIt would be nice if these parameters could be made available (and the output file recovered) in the next iteration of the screen.seqs wrapper.\n\nThis is not a major issue so it can probably wait for the major update of the wrapper (migration to Mothur 1.39.5).\n\nThanks in advance for the enhancements :)\n\nping @shiltemann","files":null}]}